New Records: Adam Zampa became the tournament’s leading wicket-taker.
Key Match Events: Marnus Labuschagne top-scored with 71 runs for Australia.
Adam Zampa took 3 wickets for 21 runs, including key dismissals of Ben Stokes and Moeen Ali.
Mitchell Starc dismissed Jonny Bairstow on the first ball of the second innings.
Ben Stokes scored 64 runs and was pivotal in England's chase.
David Warner caught Moeen Ali in the deep off Adam Zampa.
Chris Woakes took 4 wickets for 54 runs.
Adil Rashid took 2 wickets for 38 runs.
Australia bowled out England with 33 runs to spare.
Pre-Game Insights: Jos Buttler won the toss and chose to field first.
Post-Match Reflections: Australia's win sees them put one foot into the semi-finals.
England's sixth defeat sees them mathematically out of contention to finish in the top four.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Australian team wore black armbands in memory of Mitchell Marsh's grandfather.
Mitch Marsh will rejoin the squad in Mumbai by Monday.
